  "prompt": "I have heard Reliance JIO locks a mobile phone and the same cannot be used for any other network. Is it true?",
  "response": "No, this is not entirely true. Reliance Jio does not permanently lock phones to its network. Here are the key points:\n\n1. When you purchase a Jio SIM or phone through Jio, the device might have some initial restrictions.\n\n2. Jio used to have a practice of providing phones with initial lock-in periods, but these are temporary and can be unlocked.\n\n3. If you buy a phone through Jio's device financing scheme, there might be certain conditions during the repayment period.\n\n4. Once you complete any financial obligations, the phone can be used with any other telecom operator's SIM card.\n\n5. Most modern smartphones sold by Jio are unlocked and can accept SIM cards from other networks.\n\n6. You can easily port your number to another network or use a different SIM card in a Jio-purchased phone.\n\nThe misconception about permanent network locking is not accurate. Jio follows standard telecom practices and does not permanently restrict phone usage to its network.\n\nIf you have specific concerns about a particular device, it's best to check the exact terms of purchase or contact Jio customer support directly.",
